  "title": "throw an error if refresh was called before start",
  "body": "<!--\r\n  Thanks for participating in this project! We will try to answer as soon as possible 🙏\r\n-->\r\n\r\n**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe 🙏**\r\n\r\nWhen Implementing Vue InstantSearch, I used `refresh` bound to the wrong \"this\", which silently didn't work\r\n\r\n**Describe the solution you'd like 🤔**\r\n\r\nChange the guard from \"this.helper\" to \"this.isStarted\" and throw an error \"can not call refresh before start\" if it hasn't started\r\n\r\n**Describe alternatives you've considered ✨**\r\n\r\n* Removing the guard all together, but the error would be cryptic\r\n* move InstantSearch from a class to a factory so it doesn't need to be bound anymore\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/a35cb0b7bc0cfbd83fa98648db31f0a6d002dd2f/src/lib/InstantSearch.js#L312-L316\r\n",
